&nbsp;Starting and Stopping the Server&nbsp; In most use cases, the YarraServer process is controlled via the WebGUI. However, it is also possible to control the server using command-line tools. &nbsp;
If Running as Linux Daemon When the YarraServer has been installed as daemon (recommended and described here), the YarraServer can be started using a terminal shell (as user yarraserver) and typing:
sudo systemctl start yarra The server is now running in the background.
